            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne botan. Garden, ¶ 26/8/70 ¶ This letter is dated 26/8 but registered 30/8 which suggests that the transfers dated 29/8 were sent at the same time and belong with this letter, rather than bein...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">70.08.26<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Odgers</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">V70/10155, unit 469, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">Trans. Angela. To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">18 August 1870</seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to J. McCulloch,11 September 1870.</p>
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">There are two letters to McC 18 Augus</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">t</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>labelled 18 August 1870;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg rend="HTMLCite"
                          style="font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; color: #C00000; ">70-08-18b</seg>
                     <seg rend="HTMLCite"
                          style="font-style: italic; font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg rend="HTMLCite"
                          style="font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; color: #C00000; ">is reg entry only about Ferguson's quarters; the other 70-08-18 looks as if it is the one meant BUT it is dated in the transcript as 18/</seg>
                     <seg rend="HTMLCite"
                          style="font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; color: #C00000; background-color: #FFFF00; ">5</seg>
                     <seg rend="HTMLCite"
                          style="font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; color: #C00000; ">/70.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg rend="HTMLCite"
                          style="font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; color: #C00000; ">I think from context of this group of letters that the file name is right, and the transcription for May is wrong. Please check the source document</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Melbourne botan. Garden,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">26/8/70<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">This letter is dated 26/8 but registered 30/8 which suggests that the transfers dated 29/8 were sent at the same time and belong with this letter, rather than being a separate letter. See below.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It having been decided by the honorable the Chief Secretary, that no supplementary expenditure should be incurred in the botanic Garden in 1870, I have now the honor to propose the following transfer, as I feel myself extremely embarrassed to make reductions in the wages vote, because there employees, whom I can best spare claim seniority, and to deprive the establishment of the best, zealous and modest workers, simply because they may happen to be a few years less employed, would be detrimental to the best interests of the service. The reductions now proposed through transfer of some votes to the wages funds will not completely provide for the full pay of every employee til the end of the year, but render the discharge of any of them not necessary for some months to come. I beg also to remark, that it is not without sadness, that I propose these reductions, because after the enormous decrease of the estimates for 1870, which has fallen far more severely on the Department under my control than on most offices, the service here in all branches is already very much circumscribed, and thus the transfer of the small special votes for publishing works, travelling expenses, aviary forage renders some branches of the service for the time annihilated; and I beg respectfully to add, that while I make this great sacrifice for the time, it must be distinctly understood, that the transfer this time proposed is not to imply a recommendation of mine, to do away with these items on future estimates, but on the contrary I shall probably find it necessary to recommend next year a recompensing transfer from the wages vote to that of literary work &amp;c, as I cannot think that it is the wish of the honorable the Chief Secretary to abolish any of the workings of my establishment, all having proved instructive and remunerative and all standing in need of being continued for the best interests of the country.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Director of the botan. Garden.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The Undersecretary</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Transfer proposed for favorable consideration of the hon.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">the Chief Secretary</hi>
               </seg>
            </p>
