            </table>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd von Mueller M.D.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Direct. botan. Garden</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">29/8/70<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">The main letter was registered on 30 August 1870</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">,</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>evidently including the proposal for the Chief Secretary dated 29 August.</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>Odgers<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">minuted</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">:</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">replied<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-weight: bold; background-color: #FFFF00; ">date cut off p/c</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>September 1870:</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'As there is not in any instance a sum unauthorized sufficient to admit of the proposed transfers will Dr von Mueller be so good as to indicate the Authorities to be<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <hi rend="underline">cancelled</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>with the amount of such cancellations respectively'. The letter was referred to Mueller on 10 September and he returned it to the Chief Secretary's Department on 13 September.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">M supplied the requested list of authorities to be cancelled in M to J. McCulloch, 11 September</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; background-color: #FFFF00; ">The date</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is almost certainly 9 <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>or 10 September given 70-09-11b, which answers Odgers question</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">, evidently in response to Odgers' minute. I think we can still set this as final if we delete the part indicated; I am assuming Odgers' reply is a minute.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
